<subSubSection pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
The specimen is not an aviculariine since it has no spatulate scopulae, bears two rounded spermathecae, and has no type II urticating setae (Fig. 224). The type locality, spermathecae morphology (Fig. 223) and presence of urticating setae type III match with the diagnostic characteristics of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Thrixopelma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thrixopelma" order="Araneae" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Thrixopelma</taxonomicName>
species. Thus, we transfer 
<taxonomicName authority="Koch, 1850" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1850" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Eurypelma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurypelma aymara" order="Araneae" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aymara">Eurypelma aymara</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Thrixopelma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thrixopelma" order="Araneae" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Thrixopelma</taxonomicName>
, making the new combination 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Thrixopelma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thrixopelma aymara" order="Araneae" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aymara">Thrixopelma aymara</taxonomicName>
(Chamberlin, 1916) comb. n.
</paragraph>
